
    Tangled Venezuelan paraglider rescued from power lines

        

    
        
                
                Image copyright
                 Twitter/@corpoelectachir
                
            
            
        Power cuts are frequent in Venezuela.The eastern state of TÃ¡chira is one of the worst hit with residents complaining that they often spend up to eight hours without power.The state-run power corporation Corpoelec rarely gives reasons for the cuts, while the government has in the past blamed "saboteurs".But on Sunday, Corpoelec was quick to say it would have to turn off the power - to free a paraglider who had become tangled in its power lines.
    
      
              
